items.sentence: You know I'm supposed to be doing that today, don't you?
I wonder who Tom thinks Mary thinks is going to do that.
It turns out that Tom is younger than he told me he was.
Tom didn't start studying French until after he retired.
I know what I have to do, but I'm not sure how to do it.
The other day, I met one of my classmates on the street.
If I'd known your address, I would've sent you a letter.
I found what I was looking for in the back of my closet.
I might be the only one who knows why we should do that.
I plan to do that every Monday for the rest of the year.
